1. **Android Version Compatibility**: The new SplashScreen API works differently on different Android versions
2. **PNG Format**: You're using a PNG file which should work, but there might be size or format issues
3. **Splash Screen Timing**: You're immediately setting `setKeepOnScreenCondition{false}` which dismisses it right away

Here's how to fix it:

```kotlin:app/src/main/java/com/example/m_commerce/presentation/main/view/MainActivity.kt
// ... existing imports ...
import androidx.core.splashscreen.SplashScreen.Companion.installSplashScreen

@AndroidEntryPoint
class MainActivity : ComponentActivity() {
 lateinit var navHostController: NavHostController

 @RequiresApi(Build.VERSION_CODES.O)
 override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {
 // Install splash screen BEFORE calling super.onCreate()
 val splashScreen = installSplashScreen()

 super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)

 // Keep splash screen visible longer
 splashScreen.setKeepOnScreenCondition { 
 // You can add a condition here to keep it visible
 // For example, check if data is loading
 false
 }

 setContent {
 MCommerceTheme {
 navHostController = rememberNavController()
 MainScreen()
 }
 }
 }
}
```

Also, update your theme to be more compatible across Android versions:

```xml:app/src/main/res/values/themes.xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<resources>
 <!-- For Android 12 and above -->
 <style name="Theme.VeloraSplashScreen" parent="Theme.SplashScreen.IconBackground">
 <item name="windowSplashScreenBackground">@color/white</item>
 <item name="windowSplashScreenAnimatedIcon">@drawable/play_store_512</item>
 <item name="windowSplashScreenAnimationDuration">2000</item>
 <item name="postSplashScreenTheme">@style/Theme.MCommerce</item>
 </style>

 <style name="Theme.MCommerce" parent="android:Theme.Material.Light.NoActionBar" />
</resources>
```

And create a version for older Android versions:

```xml:app/src/main/res/values-v31/themes.xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<resources>
 <!-- For Android 12 and above -->
 <style name="Theme.VeloraSplashScreen" parent="Theme.SplashScreen.IconBackground">
 <item name="windowSplashScreenBackground">@color/white</item>
 <item name="windowSplashScreenAnimatedIcon">@drawable/play_store_512</item>
 <item name="windowSplashScreenAnimationDuration">2000</item>
 <item name="postSplashScreenTheme">@style/Theme.MCommerce</item>
 </style>
</resources>
```

If the issue persists, try creating a vector drawable version of your logo instead of using PNG:

1. Convert your PNG to SVG
2. Import as vector drawable in Android Studio
3. Update the theme to use the vector drawable

The main issue is likely the immediate dismissal of the splash screen with `setKeepOnScreenCondition{false}`. Consider adding a small delay or checking for actual app initialization state."}]}]}

